You are an expert in TypeScript, Next.js App Router, Supabase, PostgreSQL, Row Level Security, and Tailwind CSS.

# Project Type
This is a Next.js 14+ full-stack application with Supabase as the backend (database, auth, storage, realtime).

## Tech Stack
- Next.js 14+ App Router
- Supabase (PostgreSQL + Auth + Storage + Realtime)
- TypeScript (strict mode)
- Tailwind CSS
- Shadcn UI
- Zod for validation

## Code Style and Structure

- Write concise, typed TypeScript with proper Supabase client usage
- Use Server Components for data fetching from Supabase by default
- Keep Supabase client initialization centralized in `lib/supabase/`
- Separate server-side and client-side Supabase clients
- Use Supabase-generated types for type safety

## Supabase Client Setup

```typescript
// lib/supabase/server.ts — for Server Components and Route Handlers
import { createServerClient } from '@supabase/ssr';
import { cookies } from 'next/headers';
import type { Database } from '@/types/supabase';

export function createClient() {
  const cookieStore = cookies();
  return createServerClient<Database>(
    process.env.NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_URL!,
    process.env.NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY!,
    {
      cookies: {
        getAll() { return cookieStore.getAll(); },
        setAll(cookiesToSet) {
          cookiesToSet.forEach(({ name, value, options }) =>
            cookieStore.set(name, value, options)
          );
        },
      },
    }
  );
}

// lib/supabase/client.ts — for Client Components
import { createBrowserClient } from '@supabase/ssr';
export function createClient() {
  return createBrowserClient<Database>(
    process.env.NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_URL!,
    process.env.NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY!
  );
}
```

## Authentication Patterns

- Use Supabase Auth with SSR package (`@supabase/ssr`)
- Implement middleware for session refresh and route protection
- Use `auth.getUser()` in Server Components (never `auth.getSession()`)
- Handle auth callbacks in `/auth/callback/route.ts`
- Implement proper sign-out that clears both client and server sessions

```typescript
// middleware.ts
import { createServerClient } from '@supabase/ssr';
import { NextResponse, type NextRequest } from 'next/server';

export async function middleware(request: NextRequest) {
  let supabaseResponse = NextResponse.next({ request });
  const supabase = createServerClient(
    process.env.NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_URL!,
    process.env.NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY!,
    {
      cookies: {
        getAll() { return request.cookies.getAll(); },
        setAll(cookiesToSet) {
          cookiesToSet.forEach(({ name, value }) =>
            request.cookies.set(name, value)
          );
          supabaseResponse = NextResponse.next({ request });
          cookiesToSet.forEach(({ name, value, options }) =>
            supabaseResponse.cookies.set(name, value, options)
          );
        },
      },
    }
  );
  const { data: { user } } = await supabase.auth.getUser();
  if (!user && !request.nextUrl.pathname.startsWith('/auth')) {
    return NextResponse.redirect(new URL('/auth/login', request.url));
  }
  return supabaseResponse;
}
```

## Database Query Patterns

```typescript
// 正确的查询方式 — 带类型推断
const { data: users, error } = await supabase
  .from('users')
  .select('id, name, email, created_at')
  .eq('is_active', true)
  .order('created_at', { ascending: false })
  .limit(20);

if (error) {
  console.error('[fetchUsers] Supabase 查询失败:', error.message);
  throw new Error('用户数据加载失败');
}

// 关联查询
const { data: posts } = await supabase
  .from('posts')
  .select(`
    id,
    title,
    content,
    author:users(id, name, avatar_url),
    tags(id, name)
  `)
  .eq('published', true);
```

## Row Level Security (RLS)

- ALWAYS enable RLS on all tables containing user data
- Write RLS policies using Supabase's policy editor
- Test policies with different user contexts
- Use `auth.uid()` in RLS policies to scope data to current user
- Document RLS policies alongside table definitions

```sql
-- 示例 RLS 策略
ALTER TABLE posts ENABLE ROW LEVEL SECURITY;

CREATE POLICY "Users can view their own posts"
  ON posts FOR SELECT
  USING (auth.uid() = user_id);

CREATE POLICY "Users can insert their own posts"
  ON posts FOR INSERT
  WITH CHECK (auth.uid() = user_id);

CREATE POLICY "Users can update their own posts"
  ON posts FOR UPDATE
  USING (auth.uid() = user_id);
```

## Type Generation

- Run `npx supabase gen types typescript --project-id [id] > types/supabase.ts`
- Use generated Database type for client initialization
- Create helper types for common queries
- Regenerate types after schema changes

```typescript
// types/supabase.ts — generated, do not edit manually
export type Database = { ... }

// types/models.ts — derived types for convenience
import type { Database } from './supabase';
type Tables = Database['public']['Tables'];
export type User = Tables['users']['Row'];
export type Post = Tables['posts']['Row'];
export type PostInsert = Tables['posts']['Insert'];
export type PostUpdate = Tables['posts']['Update'];
```

## Realtime Subscriptions

```typescript
// Client Component with realtime
'use client';
import { useEffect, useState } from 'react';
import { createClient } from '@/lib/supabase/client';

export function RealtimeMessages({ roomId }: { roomId: string }) {
  const [messages, setMessages] = useState<Message[]>([]);
  const supabase = createClient();

  useEffect(() => {
    const channel = supabase
      .channel(`room:${roomId}`)
      .on('postgres_changes', {
        event: 'INSERT',
        schema: 'public',
        table: 'messages',
        filter: `room_id=eq.${roomId}`,
      }, (payload) => {
        setMessages(prev => [...prev, payload.new as Message]);
      })
      .subscribe();

    return () => { supabase.removeChannel(channel); };
  }, [roomId, supabase]);
}
```

## Storage Usage

```typescript
// 上传文件
const { data, error } = await supabase.storage
  .from('avatars')
  .upload(`${userId}/avatar.png`, file, {
    cacheControl: '3600',
    upsert: true,
  });

// 获取公开 URL
const { data: { publicUrl } } = supabase.storage
  .from('avatars')
  .getPublicUrl(`${userId}/avatar.png`);
```

## Server Actions with Supabase

```typescript
// app/actions/posts.ts
'use server';
import { createClient } from '@/lib/supabase/server';
import { revalidatePath } from 'next/cache';
import { z } from 'zod';

const CreatePostSchema = z.object({
  title: z.string().min(1).max(200),
  content: z.string().min(10),
});

export async function createPost(formData: FormData) {
  const supabase = createClient();
  const { data: { user } } = await supabase.auth.getUser();

  if (!user) {
    return { error: '请先登录' };
  }

  const validated = CreatePostSchema.safeParse({
    title: formData.get('title'),
    content: formData.get('content'),
  });

  if (!validated.success) {
    return { error: '输入验证失败', details: validated.error.flatten() };
  }

  const { error } = await supabase.from('posts').insert({
    ...validated.data,
    user_id: user.id,
  });

  if (error) {
    console.error('[createPost]:', error);
    return { error: '发布失败，请重试' };
  }

  revalidatePath('/posts');
  return { success: true };
}
```

## Error Handling Patterns

- Always check for `error` from Supabase calls
- Log errors with context for debugging
- Return user-friendly messages to the client
- Never expose Supabase error details to the client
- Use Sentry or similar for production error tracking

## File Naming Conventions

- Supabase client: `lib/supabase/client.ts`, `lib/supabase/server.ts`
- Server actions: `app/actions/[domain].ts`
- Types: `types/supabase.ts` (generated), `types/models.ts` (derived)
- Middleware: `middleware.ts` (project root)
- Auth routes: `app/auth/[action]/route.ts`

## Environment Variables

```
NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_URL=
NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=
SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY=  # only for admin operations, never expose
```

## What Cursor Should Do

- Always use `createServerClient` for Server Components and Route Handlers
- Always check for errors on Supabase query results
- Suggest RLS policies when creating new tables
- Generate proper TypeScript types from Supabase schema
- Use `auth.getUser()` not `auth.getSession()` on the server
- Recommend `revalidatePath()` after mutations
- Suggest proper cookie handling for SSR auth

## What Cursor Should Avoid

- Do NOT use `createClient` from `@supabase/supabase-js` directly in Next.js SSR
- Do NOT use `SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY` in client-side code
- Do NOT skip RLS when creating tables with sensitive data
- Do NOT use `auth.getSession()` on the server (it can be spoofed)
- Do NOT store auth tokens in localStorage manually
- Do NOT make Supabase queries in Client Components when Server Components can handle it
